I have to admit that I have only had their Hot and Sour Soup and Beef with Green Beans, for take out.  I’ve been searching for excellent Hot and Sour soup since one of my favorite restaurants closed and so I have a good basis for comparison. This is delicious. Thick, hearty, loaded with tree fungus (mushrooms) and other traditional vegetables, it has a little kick to it but isn’t so spicy that I can’t enjoy it.  I happen to like mine with a good bit of the sour flavor, so I sometimes add a dash of rice vinegar when I get it home.  It was my “go to” on a cold winter evening.  This isn’t a place you’d think of trying based on curb appeal...there isn’t any.  I decided to try it because I  drove by anyway and I was still on my quest for the perfect H & S soup.  I enjoyed the beef with green beans but it wasn’t memorable.  I tried the fried rice once and it disappointed.  Take the food home...the interior is dreary. But it has an open kitchen so I can see that it looks clean.  And very budget friendly.

I am not a big fan of Chinese food in general, but this place is actually pretty good.  It is a takeout place so don't expect any service, but food is good and portions are big.  I always order Sichuan bean curd with broccoli and boneless spare ribs.  Both are great.  We also tried fried rice: it is made to order not precooked.  Other dishes are hit-and-miss, but in general food is certainly better than average and not greasy like many other Chinese places.  Not sure why so low ratings....

I've really been happy with Asia Wok over the years.  In particular, they use a different filling for their egg rolls than most other Chinese restaurants in the area.  Much better, in my opinion.  As far as entrees go, I haven't been too adventurous: chicken & broccoli, chicken w/cashews, moo shu X.  Not a fan of the last two: celery does _not_ go with cashew chicken, and the moo shu has a bland, slightly bitter taste.  The chicken with broccoli is always good, however, as are the dumplings.  Asia Wok isn't going to beat places in Chinatown, but it's my favorite "late-night" Chinese in the Waltham/Watertown/West Newton area.  Way better than Hon Dynasty, Dragon Chef, or Tiki House.
